Using the Vector API
--------------------

Loop over vector, setting each key `i` equal to `i`:

<br>

\begin{code}
{-@ initialize :: n:Nat -> IdVec n @-}
initialize n      = loop 0 empty
  where
    loop i a 
      | i < n     = let a' = set i i a
                    in
                        loop (i+1) a'
      | otherwise = a 
\end{code}

